name: Cycles Model
description: Cycles is a daily time-step agroecosystem model that simulates the biophysical processes and management practices occurring within cropping systems and other landuses. Processes include fluxes in the water and energy balance, the coupled cycling of carbon and nitrogen, and plant growth. The model can simulate a wide range of agricultural management practices such as tillage, organic and inorganic nutrient additions, annual and perennial crops, crop harvests as grain or forages, polycultures and relay cropping, grazing, and irrigation. Crop growth is represented with a generalizable framework such that a nearly limitless variety of agricultural crop species can be specified by the user. A user reference guide for Cycles is provided at PSUModeling.GitHub.io/Cycles/.

maintainer.name: Armen Kemanian, Lorne Leonard, Varun Ratnakar

parameters.name: country
parameters.description: Country to run the simulation for

parameters.name: crop_name
parameters.description: Name of the crop to run the simulation for

parameters.name: start_planting_day
parameters.description: Day of the year for the start of the planting window

parameters.name: fertilizer_rate
parameters.description: Mass of nitrogen fertilizer added each year (kg/ha). The model will multiply the mass by the concentration of the fertilizer (1)

parameters.name: weed_fraction
parameters.description: Areal fraction of weed: 0.05 is low, 0.25 is moderate, 1 is high, and 2 is the maximum (after 2 there will be no response from the model)
